            "title": "FDA requires additional MRI scan for Alzheimer's patients on Biogen's Leqembi due to safety concerns. Drug aims to slow disease progression by targeting beta-amyloid plaques. FDA approved in 2023.",
            "id": "a29ee0f7-3091-40fe-9529-2cea5eff246b",
            "description": "The FDA has mandated an additional MRI scan for Alzheimer's patients using Leqembi (lecanemab) due to safety concerns related to a rare but potentially fatal side effect. Biogen Inc.'s Leqembi, designed to slow Alzheimer's progression in individuals with mild cognitive impairment or early-stage dementia, was granted FDA approval in 2023. This therapy targets beta-amyloid plaques, protein buildup in the brain associated with the disease's advancement. The drug's goal is to lessen these plaques to help maintain cognitive function. For more details, refer to the Benzinga.com website.",
